# Fusion 0.2 Hydration UI

UI templates are authored visually in Roblox Studio. Code binds reactive logic to them using Fusion 0.2's `Hydrate`.

## Hydration Pattern

```luau
local Fusion = require(ReplicatedStorage.Packages.Fusion)
local Value = Fusion.Value
local Computed = Fusion.Computed
local Hydrate = Fusion.Hydrate

local function init()
    local someState = Value(initialValue)

    local template = playerGui:WaitForChild("TemplateName")
    Hydrate(template) {
        Text = Computed(function()
            return tostring(someState:get())
        end),
    }
end
```

## Fusion 0.2 API (no scopes)

- `Value(initial)` -- mutable reactive state; read with `:get()`, write with `:set(v)`
- `Computed(fn)` -- derived state; fn reads other values via `:get()`
- `Hydrate(instance) { ... }` -- bind reactive properties to an existing instance
- `Spring(goal, speed?, damping?)` -- spring animation toward a reactive goal
- `Tween(goal, tweenInfo)` -- tween toward a reactive goal
- `Observer(value):onChange(fn)` -- watch a value for changes
- `OnEvent(eventName)` / `OnChange(propertyName)` -- keys for Hydrate tables

## px Scaling (device-universal UI)

Design all UI at **1920x1080**. Use `px.luau` to scale pixel values to the current device:

```luau
local px = require("@utils/px")

-- Call once at UI root
px.connectViewport()

-- Use in Hydrate calls -- returns Fusion Computed values
Hydrate(frame) {
    Size = px.offset(300, 200),           -- scaled UDim2.fromOffset
    Position = px.udim2(0.5, -150, 0, 40), -- UDim2 with scaled offsets
}

-- For single values (font size, corner radius, padding)
local fontSize = px(18) -- Computed that returns scaled integer
```

### px API

| Function | Returns | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `px(n)` | `Computed<number>` | Scaled + rounded pixel value |
| `px.scale(n)` | `Computed<number>` | Scaled pixel (no rounding, for animations) |
| `px.offset(x, y)` | `Computed<UDim2>` | `UDim2.fromOffset` with scaled values |
| `px.udim2(sx, ox, sy, oy)` | `Computed<UDim2>` | Full UDim2 with scaled offsets |
| `px.udim(s, o)` | `Computed<UDim>` | UDim with scaled offset |
| `px.connectViewport()` | void | Connect to camera viewport (call once) |

## Rules

- **No full-code UI construction** -- do not build complex UIs from scratch in code; design them in Studio
- Use `Hydrate` to bind reactive state to Studio templates
- Use `px()` for all pixel measurements to ensure device scaling
- Hydration controllers go in `game/shared/controllers/`
- Reusable Fusion hooks go in `game/shared/hooks/`
- One controller per UI screen/feature
